00:53:09.930 --> 00:53:12.850
like you to actually
mobilize you on that.

00:53:12.850 --> 00:53:15.020
We need to catch up
on a number of things

00:53:15.020 --> 00:53:16.045
in terms of our systems.

00:53:19.560 --> 00:53:21.940
We're better at medical
technology, of course,

00:53:21.940 --> 00:53:23.630
because this is our priority.

00:53:23.630 --> 00:53:27.180
We also have a number
of people working

00:53:27.180 --> 00:53:29.490
on innovations in logistics.

00:53:29.490 --> 00:53:32.440
This is an area
that is interesting.

00:53:32.440 --> 00:53:35.670
I've been supporting
one of our teams

00:53:35.670 --> 00:53:40.820
who was asked to look,
for example, after Haiti,

00:53:40.820 --> 00:53:49.390
at the management of
waste, because in most

00:53:49.390 --> 00:53:53.110
of the countries, you actually
don't have the industry that

00:53:53.110 --> 00:53:55.450
can eliminate some waste.

00:53:55.450 --> 00:53:55.990
Right?

00:53:55.990 --> 00:53:57.720
So we have our own incinerators.

00:53:57.720 --> 00:54:00.695
But an incinerator does
not eliminate everything.

00:54:03.720 --> 00:54:08.170
And we needed to
figure out whether it

00:54:08.170 --> 00:54:11.110
was better to create our
own management on site,

00:54:11.110 --> 00:54:14.380
or to export our
waste, and make sure

00:54:14.380 --> 00:54:17.370
that it is done in a safe
way in another country.

00:54:17.370 --> 00:54:20.610
In the case of
Haiti, we've actually

00:54:20.610 --> 00:54:24.200
concluded that it was better
to reexport the waste.

00:54:24.200 --> 00:54:25.040
And it's been done.

00:54:25.040 --> 00:54:29.020
We had a contract with
a company in the US

00:54:29.020 --> 00:54:33.110
